3.Complate description and build exactly as it wrote


 A waterfall process requires a team to write down a complete description of the software at the beginning of the project, and
then build exactly what they wrote.

• The waterfall process made it difficult to respond to change because of the focus on documentation rather than collaboration.

• There is no silver bullet process or practice that makes projects run perfectly.

• Teams that make waterfall work do it by adopting eﬀective so ware practices and principles, especially ones that improve communication
